      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-02-02T19:27:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Also, the context fill paint may carry deferred opacity.  I think we need to pass that to drawImageRect too.",
      "parentUuid": "197f9187_36e8010e",
      "revId": "3062cc1171d35ac929b5d182304ac8afbf574239",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "72d0080f_f8087bbe",
        "filename": "modules/svg/src/SkSVGImage.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 70,
      "author": {
        "id": 10818
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-02-02T20:00:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "drawImageRect - done, although it will need further tweaking I think to support preserveAspectRatio\n\nRe: opacity, I couldn\u0027t find anything in the spec about fill/stroke paints affecting the image. I also played around in Chrome but the only attribute I found that did affect the image was the overall \u0027opacity\u0027 attribute. What do you think?",
      "parentUuid": "0dd4ed70_f34daa3d",
      "revId": "3062cc1171d35ac929b5d182304ac8afbf574239",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fe50a64c_4107b32f",
        "filename": "modules/svg/src/SkSVGImage.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 70,
      "author": {
        "id": 5641
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-02-02T20:11:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "True, fill/stroke paints are a poor match.\n\nI was thinking we\u0027re not observing \u0027opacity\u0027 here because \u003cimage\u003e is a leaf node and its opacity should be applied via paint (not layer).  But the leaf opacity optimization in RenderContext checks for the presence of fill/stroke explicitly and falls back to using a layer when neither is present: https://github.com/google/skia/blob/28f702ca8fb56e960d6ed8257ccba3012ab1199a/modules/svg/src/SkSVGRenderContext.cpp#L284\n\nSo I guess it works fine, if not optimal.  Maybe we can circle back and relax the heuristic later if needed.",
      "parentUuid": "72d0080f_f8087bbe",
      "revId": "3062cc1171d35ac929b5d182304ac8afbf574239",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    }
